Callback functions
  A callback is a function passed as an argument to another function and executed later.
  Used for non-sync operations
  Eg: after reading data from file Node JS(it reads in async way) don't know what to do next therefore it needed callback functions.

Express
  Express.js is a minimal, fast web framework for Node.js used to build web servers and APIs easily.

